#CometLanding Press briefings near landing day  streamed live at &
#CometLanding Live coverage of the Go/No-Go decisions during Nov 11th & 12th  will be on ESA TV and on Twitter.
#CometLanding Taking into account signal travel time  confirmation of landing is expected around 10:00 AM CST.
#CometLanding Rosetta will release Philae at 2:35 AM CST on Nov 12th  with landing about 7 hrs later at Agilkia.
#CometLanding This shows a close-up of landing site Agilkia  about 300 meters wide by 600 meters long.
#CometLanding A nice photo of the region around Agilkia on the small lobe of the comet  from about 25 km.
#CometLanding A nice photo of the small lobe of comet 67P  from about 25 km.
#CometLanding The landing site is named for Agilkia Island  on the Nile River in the south of Egypt.
#CometLanding The site where Philae lander is scheduled to touch down on Comet 67P is now called Agilkia.
#CometLanding Site J (on the smaller lobe) was finally selected as the primary landing location for Nov 12th.
#CometLanding A great many candidate landing sites made the final cut during the site selection process.
#CometLanding Project Scientist Holger Sierks presenting the early high-resolution images of comet 67P.
#CometLanding When Rosetta first caught up with the comet  Stefen Ulamec suggested some possible landing sites.
#CometLanding Project Scientist Taylor has a tattoo of the big Nov 12th Philae landing  on his upper leg.
#CometLanding Project Scientist Taylor with a full scale model of the Philae Lander  at DLR Cologne LCC  France.
